HEADWORD: Jackman
<hw>Jack"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Jackmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One wearing a jack; a horse soldier; a retainer. See
3d <er>Jack</er>, <pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Christie . . . the laird's chief <qex>jackman</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A cream cheese.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir T. Elyot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

